[6] Diarrhea, fatal - Nepal (Central region)
Date: Thu 24 Jul 2008
Source: Nepal News [edited]
<http://www.nepalnews.com/archive/2008/jul/jul24/news03.php>


At least 7 persons have died and hundreds others fallen sick due to a
serious outbreak of diarrhea in Sindhuli district in the past week.
Among those who have lost their lives to diarrhea are 2 minors.

Reports said that 5 persons died at the district hospital while
undergoing treatment whereas 2 others lost their lives in the
affected villages. It further said that hundreds of people in rural
parts of the district have taken ill after contracting a serious bout
of diarrhea-related diseases.

The district hospital said that a medical team with necessary
medicine is on the way to the affected areas. The hospital has been
receiving an average of 70 diarrhea patients everyday.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Sindhuli district is located in the Central region of Nepal as can
be seen on a map of the country at
<http://ncthakur.itgo.com/map04.htm>. - Mod.LL]

